    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\n`<BS>` is ignored several times (in the gif 5 times) after hitting the `c`+mapping with `nvim_buf_set_mark`\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/17349169/e5be7a22-6961-48bb-af19-9be80aaa935e\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Create `init.lua` with the content:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.keymap.set(\"o\", \"<M-t>\", function()\r\n  vim.api.nvim_buf_set_mark(0, \"<\", 3, 5, {})\r\n  vim.api.nvim_buf_set_mark(0, \">\", 3, 12, {})\r\n\r\n  vim.cmd(\"normal! gv\")\r\n  if vim.fn.visualmode() ~= \"v\" and vim.fn.visualmode() ~= \"\" then\r\n    vim.cmd(\"normal! v\")\r\n  end\r\nend, {})\r\n```\r\n2. Create any preset file that contains something on the line 3 between columns [5-12]. example:\r\n```txt\r\n1\r\n2\r\nsome XXXXXXXX here\r\n```\r\n3. Launch neovim:\r\n```bash\r\nnvim --clean -u ~/tmp/clean_nvim/init.lua ./preset.txt\r\n```\r\n4. Press `c<M-t>` (it will detele some text on the 3 line)\r\n5. Try to use `<BS>`\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n`vim.api.nvim_buf_set_mark` won't break `<BS>` \r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.10.0-dev-1888+g3a4aa3fc5\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nIt doesn't have nvim_buf_set_mark\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nLinux arch 6.6.1-arch1-1\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.31.0\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nGit / Aur",
    "closed_at": "2023-12-19T00:01:07Z",
