            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I figure out that count of ignored `<BS>` depends on the `vim.api.nvim_buf_set_mark` leftest column.\r\nIn the current situation the `<` has the position [3, 5] and `5` means count of ignored `<BS>`.\r\n\r\n\r\nI also figured out that `setpos` has the same behaviour if i set `off` to a non zero, for example:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.fn.setpos(\"'<\", { 0, 3, 6, 9 })\r\n```\r\nI set `off` here to `9` and it will ignore 9 `<BS>`'s\r\n\r\nI tried to understand what `off` means, but i failed.",
